Most governors, MCAs, CECs, Chief Officers and even junior staff became affluent overnight.The looting that took place in the first 5 years of devolution is incomparable. We have focused more on the central government to the extent of failing to take notice of the seemingly failed project that is devolution.
The latter was one of the defining features of the Kenya Constitution 2010, having been premised upon bringing services closer to citizens as well as promoting parity in matters development.



