Mischievous ‘idlers’
Most governors, MCAs, CECs, Chief Officers and even junior staff became affluent overnight. Contracts were not only awarded corruptly, but done so at inflated costs. County offices were abuzz with mischievous ‘idlers’ – shady tenderpreneurs, brokers, cronies, and even mistresses – all craving for a share of the new-found largesse.
Relatives and cronies of county officers were not left behind, as each jostled to be placed ‘somewhere’, even if it meant being hired to offer morning prayers.



