Off-road vehicles
Then followed the official expenditure. It began with acquisition of high end cars for governors’ offices. Other departments would follow, each going for the latest off-road vehicles – even in areas where road network wasn’t a problem.
MCAs and other officers joined the bandwagon, maximising on sitting allowances and aimlessly globetrotting in the name of benchmarking.
I recall an occasion when MCAs from my county, Vihiga, toured Israel – a dessert – to go learn farming. We are still waiting for the fruits of the excursion.
Second, there seem to be no definite command of power, much less a structure of administration, in most counties. For instance, CECs and Chief Officers have been known to defy Deputy Governors. Similarly, some governors don’t go along with their deputies.
Service delivery
Such poisoned work environments militate against service delivery. The worst is a practice where county staff deliberately undermines each other so that the victims – including governors – get pushed out on flimsy grounds. It is no wonder that most county governments are battling endless labour-related court cases which could easily be avoided.
Whereas counties experience delays of transfer of funds from the Treasury, many haven’t that they could do better if funded in good time.



