Further, the paltry collections are marred with pilferage. Worse, county assemblies have largely failed to offer oversight, but instead excelled in interfering with, nay, blackmailing the executive, in a bid to achieve selfish gain. Meanwhile, Wanjiku remains stranded between two levels of governments.
